choices.text:
1. Take a Guided Tour: Take an official tour of the Statue of Liberty and learn about its history, symbolism, and legacy.

2. Climb the Pedestal and Staircase: Get up close and personal with the Statue of Liberty by climbing up the pedestal and staircase.

3. Take a Ferry Ride to the Island: Take a ride across the New York Harbor to the Statue of Liberty Island and get some great views of the New York skyline.

4. Visit the Museum: Explore the history of the Statue of Liberty and learn about its immigrant past at the Statue of Liberty Museum.

5. Host a Special Event: Host a unique event at the Statue of Liberty and create memories that will last a lifetime.

6. Go on a Night Tour: Enjoy the beauty of the Statue of Liberty at night by taking a night tour.

7. Take a Cruise: Take a cruise around the Statue of Liberty and get some great views.

8. Buy Souvenirs: Buy a souvenir or two from the gift shop to remember your visit.

9. Take Photos: Capture the beauty of the Statue of Liberty and create some amazing photos.
